abla} \cdot \vec{B}(\vec{r},t) = 0 \] <p>Taking the Fourier transform:</p> \[\int_{-\infty}^{\infty} \vec{
abla} \cdot \vec{B}(\vec{r},t) e^{-i \omega t} dt = 0 \] <p>Bringing the divergence operator outside the integral:</p> \[  \vec{
abla} \cdot \int_{-\infty}^{\infty} \vec{B}(\vec{r},t) e^{-i \omega t} dt = 0 \] <p>Recognizing the Fourier transform:</p> \[ \vec{
abla} \cdot 	ilde{B}(\vec{r},\omega) = 0 \]

\[ \vec{
abla} 	imes \vec{E}(\vec{r},t) = -  rac{\partial \vec{B}(\vec{r},t)}{\partial t} \] <p>Taking the Fourier transform:</p> \[ \int_{-\infty}^{\infty} \vec{
abla} \   imes \vec{E}(\vec{r},t) e^{-i \omega t} dt = - \int_{-\infty}^{\infty}  rac{\partial \vec{B}(\vec{r},t)}{\partial t} e^{-i \omega t} dt  \] <p>Bringing the curl operator outside the integral:</p> \[  \vec{
abla} 	imes \int_{-\infty}^{\infty} \vec{E}(\vec{r},t) e^{-i \omega t} dt = - \int_{-\infty}^{\infty}  rac{\partial \vec{B}(\vec{r},t)}{\partial t} e^{-i \omega t} dt \] <p>Recognizing the Fourier transform on the left side:</p> \[ \vec{
abla} 	imes 	ilde{E}(\vec{r},\omega) = - \int_{-\infty}^{\infty}  rac{\partial \vec{B}(\vec{r},t)}{\partial t} e^{-i \omega t} dt \] <p>Using integration by parts on the right side:</p> \[ u = e^{-i \omega t} \quad dv =  rac{\partial \vec{B}(\vec{r},t)}{\partial t} dt \] \[ du = -i \omega e^{-i \omega t} dt \quad v = \vec{B}(\vec{r},t) \] \[ \int u \, dv = uv - \int v \, du \] \[ \int_{-\infty}^{\infty}  rac{\partial \vec{B}(\vec{r},t)}{\partial t} e^{-i \omega t} dt = \left[ \vec{B}(\vec{r},t) e^{-i \omega t} ight]_{-\infty}^{\infty} + i \omega \int_{-\infty}^{\infty} \vec{B}(\vec{r},t) e^{-i \omega t} dt \] <p>Assuming the fields vanish at infinity, the boundary term is zero:</p> \[ \int_{-\infty}^{\infty}  rac{\partial \vec{B}(\vec{r},t)}{\partial t} e^{-i \omega t} dt = i \omega 	ilde{B}(\vec{r},\omega) \] <p>Resulting in:</p> \[\vec{
abla} 	imes 	ilde{E}(\vec{r},\omega) = - i \omega 	ilde{B}(\vec{r},\omega)\]

\[ \vec{
abla} 	imes \vec{H}(\vec{r},t) = \vec{J}_{f}(\vec{r},t) +  rac{\partial \vec{D}(\vec{r},t)}{\partial t} \] <p>Taking the Fourier transform:</p> \[ \int_{-\infty}^{\infty} \vec{
abla} 	imes \vec{H}(\vec{r},t) e^{-i \omega t} dt = \int_{-\infty}^{\infty} \vec{J}_{f}(\vec{r},t) e^{-i \omega t} dt + \int_{-\infty}^{\infty}  rac{\partial \vec{D}(\vec{r},t)}{\partial t} e^{-i \omega t} dt \] <p>Bringing the curl operator outside the integral:</p> \[ \vec{
abla} 	imes \int_{-\infty}^{\infty} \vec{H}(\vec{r},t) e^{-i \omega t} dt = \int_{-\infty}^{\infty} \vec{J}_{f}(\vec{r},t) e^{-i \omega t} dt + \int_{-\infty}^{\infty}  rac{\partial \vec{D}(\vec{r},t)}{\partial t} e^{-i \omega t} dt \] <p>Recognizing the Fourier transforms on the left side and the first term on the right side:</p> \[ \vec{
abla} 	imes 	ilde{H}(\vec{r},\omega) = 	ilde{J}_{f}(\vec{r},\omega) + \int_{-\infty}^{\infty}  rac{\partial \vec{D}(\vec{r},t)}{\partial t} e^{-i \omega t} dt \] <p>Using integration by parts on the last term:</p> \[ u = e^{-i \omega t} \quad dv =  rac{\partial \vec{D}(\vec{r},t)}{\partial t} dt  \] \[  du = -i \omega e^{-i \omega t} dt \quad v = \vec{D}(\vec{r},t) \] \[  \int u \, dv = uv - \int v \, du  \] \[ \int_{-\infty}^{\infty}  rac{\partial \vec{D}(\vec{r},t)}{\partial t} e^{-i \omega t} dt = \left[ \vec{D}(\vec{r},t) e^{-i \omega t} ight]_{-\infty}^{\infty} + i \omega \int_{-\infty}^{\infty} \vec{D}(\vec{r},t) e^{-i \omega t} dt \] <p>Assuming the fields vanish at infinity, the boundary term is zero:</p> \[ \int_{-\infty}^{\infty}  rac{\partial \vec{D}(\vec{r},t)}{\partial t} e^{-i \omega t} dt = i \omega 	ilde{D}(\vec{r},\omega) \] <p>Resulting in:</p> \[  \vec{
abla} 	imes 	ilde{H}(\vec{r},\omega) = 	ilde{J}_{f}(\vec{r},\omega) + i \omega 	ilde{D}(\vec{r},\omega)  \]
